12/02/2021,"748.1331(b)(2) - Admission, Service Planning, Discharge","Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",No,12/02/2021,12/07/2021,"I:Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",Medium Low,No,"Two of two child records did not include the education, medical, or dental information. The treatment plans does not address the side effects of medication listed. ","The following corrective action plan was provided by the operation:
a.	The action(s) taken to correct each finding of non-compliance:


Additional questions were added to the preliminary service plan were the following items  questions to ask about the most recent medical exam and dental exam. If the child does not have a medical physician or a dentist, the treatment team will provide support to find a provider(s) and set up an appointment post discharge. 

Educational needs will be indicated in the preliminary treatment plan next to the educational domain. If the educational needs are not known at the time of the completion of the preliminary service plan, the teacher will consult with the childs educational institution for needs. 

Side effects of medications, question will be asked up on admission by the admitting nurse and will be indicated on the preliminary treatment plan by the clinical team. Follow up will be included in our bi-weekly updates if any side effects should be experienced by the child. 

b.	The anticipated or requested time frame for completion of each corrective action not yet complete at the time of POC submission to the Division:
Update and change was completed on 12/03/2021. 

c.	A plan for quality assurance activities intended to ensure ongoing compliance:
The clinical director will assess each plan when signing all documentation and will report during the next quarterly performance improvement committee meeting on compliance with this item. They will audit ten charts from the previous quarter and report back the percentage of compliance. This will remain an item until the compliance remains at 100% for two quarters in a row.

d.	The name(s) of each individual responsible for ensuring the implementation of each corrective action:
Clinical Director. 
"
