02/26/2021,748.2003(b)(3) - Medication,Medication,No,03/02/2021,03/05/2021,L:Medication,Medium High,Yes,"While reviewing the medication and the logs, five out of five children records had errors including inadequate pill count.","I, Athenia Gordon RCCR Inspector received email documentation of the correction for the citation given during the inspection. It states the following:
Corrective Action #1: Nurses will perform a physical count of all ordered medications upon opening a sealed bottle or receiving a new prescription bottle from a pharmacy. This count will be the starting quantity for medication inventory. Corrective Action #2: When a client is temporarily treated at a higher level of care, nurses will document on the MAR that medication was NOT administered due to client hospitalized outside the facility. Corrective Action #3: Orders to note start date upon receipt of verbal or written consent of parent/guardian and receipt of medication.
To ensure on-going compliance, the Nurse Manager or designee will complete weekly chart audits and a monthly Medication Storage Checklist (see attached). The results of these audits will be reported and reviewed in the next Quarterly Quality, Compliance and Safety meeting. Improvement efforts and interventions to increase and maintain compliance will also be included in the minutes.
Compliance was met.     -AJG"
